    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>bash is fine, but I want to try something different and see if I like it.
zsh seems to be a pretty popular alternative among some groups,
so.. why not? lets have some fun with it.</p>

<ol>
<li>follow <a href="https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh">oh-my-zsh repository</a>
to get some really fancy settings.</li>
<li>choose your favorite themes from <a href="https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/wiki/Themes">oh-my-zsh themes</a>, or you can customize your own for sure.</li>
</ol>


<p>What I need from a shell prompt are basically</p>

<ul>
<li>current working dir</li>
<li>git info</li>
</ul>


<p>the git_prompt_info comes with oh-my-zsh won&#8217;t display a thing when you are not
on any branch, that&#8217;s not acceptable for me.. I want to know I&#8217;m currently in
some git repository even not on any branch.</p>

<p>so I end up using something between the bira and candy themes,
but with bash&#8217;s git-completion.</p>

